article.headline: Montana 87, South Dakota State 47
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. (AP)Jordan Hasquet scored 17 points and Matt Dlouhy added 16, to lead Montana to an 87-47 basketball victory over South Dakota State on Sunday. The Jackrabbits (2-9) took an early 5-0 lead over the Grizzlies, but Montana took control with a 36-6 run capped by a Ryan Staudacher 3-pointer, with 9:01 left in the first half. During the run, the Griz (5-5) shot 8 of 11 from behind the arc with Hasquet scoring 9 points on three 3-pointers. As a team, Montana shot 70.6 percent from the 3-point zone in the first half, going 12 of 17. Six Montana players made 3-pointers in the half, giving the Griz a halftime lead of 57-22. Kai Williams led the Jackrabbits with 12 points and seven rebounds. In the second half, Montana continued to extend its lead with a 3-pointer from Dlouhy, making the score 79-36 with 6:31 to play. Throughout the second half, the Montana lead never was lower than 35 points. Thomas Bassett added 10 points for the Jackrabbits, who shot 33.3 percent from the field and were 1 of 10 from 3-point range.
